 Mining Review Africa editor Laura Cornish talks to Warren Beech, Head of Mining, Hogan Lovells and Nicholas Veltman, Partner, Hogan Lovells (Johannesburg) at the Investing in African Mining Indaba conference about the future outlook for the African mining industry. The experts examine which countries in Africa are investment hot spots, and which are struggling. They further cover the topic of technology in the sector and reflect on DMR minister Mosebenzi Zwane's inability to address South Africa's greatest topics of concern at the conference (Mining Charter III and the MPRDA Amendment) and how the sector would be affected should he be removed from Cabinet. Click below to watch the full video:  Feature image credit: Wikipedia